WEBVTT

00:12.677 --> 00:15.680
[soft jazz music]

00:15.680 --> 00:22.729
♪ ♪

00:36.326 --> 00:37.744
[bell dings]

00:37.744 --> 00:44.709
♪ ♪

01:17.701 --> 01:20.996
- There once was a little tree
growing in the forest.

01:22.831 --> 01:25.000
And this tree wanted so bad
to grow up

01:25.000 --> 01:26.751
and be the best tree
it could be,

01:26.751 --> 01:28.962
so it did everything

01:28.962 --> 01:32.007
good little trees
have always done.

01:32.007 --> 01:35.802
It drank water
through its roots, and it grew.

01:35.802 --> 01:40.056
It bathed in the sunlight,
and it grew.

01:40.056 --> 01:42.225
[soft music]

01:42.225 --> 01:44.978
It sheltered families
of birds...

01:44.978 --> 01:48.398
[chuckles]
Little animals, and it grew.

01:48.398 --> 01:52.527
♪ ♪

01:52.527 --> 01:56.990
And then one day,
a woodcutter came along,

01:56.990 --> 02:01.328
and he said,
"Well, I'm gonna cut you down."

02:01.328 --> 02:03.496
"Oh, no," said the little tree.

02:03.496 --> 02:07.125
"No, because I'm gonna grow
big and tall.

02:07.125 --> 02:09.586
"And anytime anyone
looks up towards me,

02:09.586 --> 02:11.796
"they're gonna think
of heaven."

02:11.796 --> 02:13.882
♪ ♪

02:13.882 --> 02:17.010
But with one swoop
of his axe...

02:17.010 --> 02:20.847
ooh, that woodcutter just
chopped that tree right down.

02:20.847 --> 02:23.892
♪ ♪

02:23.892 --> 02:26.269
And that tree was so sad.

02:26.269 --> 02:30.732
♪ ♪

02:30.732 --> 02:34.986
But then it was cut
into beams...

02:34.986 --> 02:37.238
and made into a cross.

02:39.449 --> 02:42.452
Jesus' cross.

02:42.452 --> 02:47.082
And now anytime
anyone looks at that tree...

02:47.082 --> 02:49.042
they think of God.

02:49.042 --> 02:54.172
♪ ♪

02:54.172 --> 02:55.799
So next time you're sad

02:55.799 --> 02:59.803
because you didn't get
what you want,

02:59.803 --> 03:02.472
you just wait.

03:04.641 --> 03:09.270
Because God has something
even better for you.

03:15.777 --> 03:18.238
[giggles]

03:20.407 --> 03:22.367
- The kids are gonna love it.

03:22.367 --> 03:25.370
[eerie music]

03:25.370 --> 03:28.998
♪ ♪

03:34.379 --> 03:37.215
[birds chirping]

03:40.427 --> 03:43.430
[baby crying]

03:50.854 --> 03:53.898
[soft, pleasant music]

03:53.898 --> 04:00.905
♪ ♪

04:14.794 --> 04:17.797
[baby wailing]

04:34.189 --> 04:38.234
[dog barking]

04:38.234 --> 04:39.861
- Oh, hi.

04:39.861 --> 04:44.657
[crying continues]

04:44.657 --> 04:47.202
- [laughs]

04:47.202 --> 04:48.578
Go, go, go, go, go.

04:48.578 --> 04:50.371
Go.

04:50.371 --> 04:53.458
[sighs]

04:53.458 --> 04:56.127
[crying continues]

04:56.127 --> 05:03.134
♪ ♪

05:14.604 --> 05:17.607
[blows nose]

05:28.117 --> 05:31.037
- I just didn't realize
today was Friday, I guess.

05:34.541 --> 05:36.584
[baby coos]

05:39.712 --> 05:41.506
It's just, why do you have
to go on the weekend?

05:41.506 --> 05:43.424
It's not right.

05:43.424 --> 05:46.010
- Honey, it's 3M.

05:46.010 --> 05:48.346
It's our biggest account yet.

05:51.015 --> 05:54.018
I can't just ask them
to shut down

05:54.018 --> 05:57.438
their entire phone system
during business hours

05:57.438 --> 05:59.691
just to fix the system
that we installed.

06:06.948 --> 06:08.783
Honey...

06:08.783 --> 06:11.286
- [softly]
I'm sorry.

06:11.286 --> 06:13.871
I just think my...

06:13.871 --> 06:17.709
my stomach is starting
to act up again--

06:17.709 --> 06:19.836
- You're getting yourself
all worked up.

06:19.836 --> 06:21.045
- I'm sorry.

06:28.511 --> 06:32.724
- I know you hate it
when I have to leave.

06:32.724 --> 06:35.226
Well, Christina will be
back later.

06:35.226 --> 06:37.228
You can play with the puppy.

06:39.188 --> 06:41.733
[baby coos]

06:41.733 --> 06:43.901
- I'm just so scared.

06:45.653 --> 06:47.530
If I'm pregnant again,

06:47.530 --> 06:49.616
there goes teaching
next semester.

06:49.616 --> 06:50.867
- Did you take the second pill?

06:50.867 --> 06:52.493
- And the vacation
is gonna be ruined.

06:52.493 --> 06:54.245
- Betty, stop.

06:54.245 --> 06:55.330
Hey.

06:56.998 --> 07:00.001
I really don't think
you're pregnant.

07:00.001 --> 07:02.086
Just take the second pill.

07:03.630 --> 07:06.090
You're torturing yourself
for no reason.

07:08.551 --> 07:11.220
- I don't like when you leave.

07:14.974 --> 07:17.268
[baby coos]
- It's just a few days.

07:17.268 --> 07:20.521
When I get back, we'll really
get down to brass tacks.

07:20.521 --> 07:22.065
We'll make a list--

07:22.065 --> 07:23.650
all the things we did before

07:23.650 --> 07:27.737
and all the things
we want to do that we missed.

07:27.737 --> 07:30.490
We'll practice our French.

07:30.490 --> 07:32.200
Ca va?

07:32.200 --> 07:34.952
- Yes.
[both chuckle]

07:34.952 --> 07:38.623
[latches snapping]

07:38.623 --> 07:41.084
Can we go back to the place
where there were no sheets?

07:41.084 --> 07:43.044
- Yeah.
- [Betty laughs]

07:43.044 --> 07:45.713
Maybe we can look
and see if--if the spoon

07:45.713 --> 07:47.465
is still there that we hid

07:47.465 --> 07:48.633
under the rock
next to the stream.

07:48.633 --> 07:50.009
- It's been ten years, Betty.

07:50.009 --> 07:51.344
- I don't know
what came over me.

07:51.344 --> 07:54.514
I just--I just took it,
and you...

07:54.514 --> 07:57.475
oh, you laughed and laughed.

07:57.475 --> 07:58.726
Said you didn't know

07:58.726 --> 08:01.062
that you had married
an international thief.

08:01.062 --> 08:04.357
- I should've suspected,
the way you stole my heart.

08:05.775 --> 08:07.652
[chuckles softly]

08:07.652 --> 08:14.659
♪ ♪

08:31.217 --> 08:33.219
- Everything's gonna be fine.

08:36.264 --> 08:39.892
[car door slams,
engine turns over]

08:42.061 --> 08:45.231
- Say, "Bye, Daddy."

08:54.282 --> 08:56.826
Okay. Okay.

08:56.826 --> 08:59.829
[distant dog barking]

09:03.833 --> 09:06.210
- But it all went boom,
remember?

09:06.210 --> 09:08.087
CANDY: Becky, glasses.

09:08.087 --> 09:10.798
JASON: When he dropped
the thing, it was like...

09:10.798 --> 09:12.425
[imitates explosion]

09:12.425 --> 09:14.969
PAT: Yeah, but Vader wasn't
on it, remember?

09:14.969 --> 09:17.680
He was out chasing
the good guys and Luke

09:17.680 --> 09:19.098
on his little ship.

09:19.098 --> 09:22.268
JASON: Oh, yeah.

09:22.268 --> 09:25.813
Oh, my gosh, that means
Vader could be in this one.

09:25.813 --> 09:27.607
PAT: I don't know, maybe.
- [chuckles]

09:27.607 --> 09:29.609
- Mom, can I have braids?

09:29.609 --> 09:31.569
- Baby, I don't think
your hair is long enough.

09:31.569 --> 09:35.323
Let's do earmuffs.
Is that okay?

09:35.323 --> 09:38.701
PAT: [as Darth Vader] Jason,
only those on the Dark Side

09:38.701 --> 09:40.912
don't use their utensils.

09:40.912 --> 09:43.331
[laughter]
CANDY: Leave him. He's eating.

09:43.331 --> 09:46.417
- And can Christina come?
She has to come.

09:46.417 --> 09:48.753
- Where?
- New Star Wars.

09:48.753 --> 09:50.713
- Okay, eat your breakfast.

09:50.713 --> 09:51.839
Pat.

09:51.839 --> 09:54.759
[indistinct chatter on radio]

09:58.054 --> 09:59.388
What you think?

09:59.388 --> 10:00.973
- I don't have
a problem with it,

10:00.973 --> 10:02.642
but do you really think
Betty's gonna agree?

10:02.642 --> 10:04.101
- I don't think Betty
will have a problem

10:04.101 --> 10:05.561
with Christina
staying another night.

10:05.561 --> 10:07.188
I mean, she's got her hands
full with that baby.

10:07.188 --> 10:10.107
- That's not what I meant,
and you know it.

10:10.107 --> 10:12.652
- If we don't take her,
she will never see it,

10:12.652 --> 10:14.445
and it's not harmful.

10:14.445 --> 10:17.490
Betty is just
an overprotective homebody.

10:17.490 --> 10:18.950
Poor thing.

10:18.950 --> 10:21.035
I don't really think
she has any fun

10:21.035 --> 10:22.370
unless she's with us.

10:22.370 --> 10:26.040
[chatter continues]

10:27.542 --> 10:30.419
- Christina, how would you
like to go see

10:30.419 --> 10:33.214
The Empire Strikes Back
with us and stay another night?

10:33.214 --> 10:35.383
[both squealing]
- [Pat chuckles]

10:35.383 --> 10:37.635
Well, I take it
you've cleared your schedule.

10:37.635 --> 10:39.512
- Yes. I just have swim today.

10:39.512 --> 10:41.389
- Okay, I can
take you there, hon.

10:41.389 --> 10:43.766
- [gasps]
- But I don't have my suit.

10:45.101 --> 10:47.103
- Of course,
I will swing by your house,

10:47.103 --> 10:48.354
and I will pick it up

10:48.354 --> 10:50.147
while the three of y'all are
at bible school.

10:50.147 --> 10:51.232
Sound good?

10:53.109 --> 10:56.153
PAT: [as Darth Vader] Jason,
may the fork be with you.

10:56.153 --> 10:57.697
[laughter]

11:00.783 --> 11:03.786
[telephone ringing]

11:09.125 --> 11:10.126
- [whispering]
Hello?

11:10.126 --> 11:12.003
- Oh, hi, Betty. It's Candy.

11:12.003 --> 11:14.338
Listen, the girls are
just having so much fun

11:14.338 --> 11:16.215
and just begged
for another night,

11:16.215 --> 11:17.967
and I know we never do
two nights in a row,

11:17.967 --> 11:20.303
but I just figured
you had your hands full

11:20.303 --> 11:22.179
with that darling baby
and that you wouldn't mind.

11:22.179 --> 11:23.848
The thing is, I'm just gonna
have to swing by

11:23.848 --> 11:26.559
and pick up
Christina's bathing suit

11:26.559 --> 11:27.727
for the swim lesson,

11:27.727 --> 11:30.396
so is there a time
that's good for you?

11:33.524 --> 11:36.652
- Um, noon.
Noon.

11:36.652 --> 11:39.447
- Hmm, yeah, I suppose
I could make that work.

11:39.447 --> 11:41.699
You know, so much to do.

11:41.699 --> 11:44.535
- You--you'll also need
peppermints

11:44.535 --> 11:47.205
because I give her one
during the swim lesson

11:47.205 --> 11:49.123
when she puts her head under.
CANDY: Peachy.

11:49.123 --> 11:50.791
All right, see ya, hon.
Bye.

11:50.791 --> 11:52.835
[line clicks]

11:52.835 --> 11:54.503
[children screaming]
Oh, no. Not me!

11:54.503 --> 11:57.590
Okay, wait! Hold on!
- Yes, you! Yes, you!

11:57.590 --> 12:00.593
[baby crying]

12:13.648 --> 12:16.651
[water running]

12:18.569 --> 12:21.572
[baby crying]

12:25.868 --> 12:28.871
[washing machine rattling]

12:31.249 --> 12:34.210
[crying continues]

12:37.964 --> 12:40.967
[vacuum whirring]

12:40.967 --> 12:43.970
[crying continues]

12:48.849 --> 12:51.018
[washing machine rattling]

12:56.190 --> 12:58.192
[button clicks, whirring stops]

12:58.192 --> 13:02.029
[washing machine rattling]

13:02.029 --> 13:05.032
[soft music]

13:05.032 --> 13:10.955
♪ ♪

13:10.955 --> 13:14.667
[indistinct chatter]

13:14.667 --> 13:15.918
CHRISTINA: Totally!

13:15.918 --> 13:17.295
BECKY: Can you please
stop sitting on me?

13:17.295 --> 13:18.629
JASON: [laughs]

13:18.629 --> 13:19.964
The sun is actually back.

13:19.964 --> 13:24.468
[indistinct chatter]

13:24.468 --> 13:26.679
- All right, y'all, let's go.

13:27.888 --> 13:30.349
- Watch out.
It's Friday the 13th.

13:30.349 --> 13:32.476
Extra bad luck.

13:34.228 --> 13:36.605
- Morning, Candy!

13:36.605 --> 13:38.274
- Hey, morning.

13:38.274 --> 13:45.281
♪ ♪

13:48.576 --> 13:51.662
Good morning, Ron.
How are we today?

13:51.662 --> 13:53.539
- Reverend.
- Reverend Ron.

13:53.539 --> 13:55.916
I'm so sorry.
That old habit is a doozy.

13:55.916 --> 13:59.545
- Mrs. Montgomery, you know,
I prefer if you knock.

13:59.545 --> 14:02.089
- You know, I just thought
I'd pop in to see

14:02.089 --> 14:04.633
if maybe, possibly, you were
gonna make an appearance today,

14:04.633 --> 14:07.178
because this is our last day
and we haven't seen you yet.

14:07.178 --> 14:09.555
- I think vacation bible school
is best left to the mothers.

14:09.555 --> 14:11.265
Don't you?
- No, I do not.

14:11.265 --> 14:13.309
Jackie used to come
and pray and sing--

14:13.309 --> 14:15.644
- Reverend Ponder's
no longer with this parish.

14:17.563 --> 14:19.815
- Yes.
[sighs]

14:19.815 --> 14:21.776
Oh, you know...

14:23.235 --> 14:26.447
Sherry Cleckler and I just
started a decorating business--

14:26.447 --> 14:28.115
the Cover Girls.

14:28.115 --> 14:29.867
We could really help you out
with all this.

14:29.867 --> 14:31.368
- [chuckles]
Oh, the one thing I do know is,

14:31.368 --> 14:34.914
I-I do not want
a feminine touch.

14:37.166 --> 14:38.542
- Okay.

14:38.542 --> 14:43.422
Well, if you change your mind,
just give me a call.

14:43.422 --> 14:45.132
[door clicks]

14:46.300 --> 14:48.010
See you soon.

14:51.514 --> 14:52.556
- Fetch.

14:54.141 --> 14:56.143
[sighs]

15:10.032 --> 15:13.244
[baby crying]

15:38.227 --> 15:41.272
[telephone ringing]

15:52.449 --> 15:54.243
- Allan. [clears throat]
- Yeah.

15:54.243 --> 15:56.704
- Betty just called.
- [groans]

15:56.704 --> 15:59.081
- To give me hell about
sending you out in the field.

15:59.081 --> 16:01.584
- I'm sorry. It's fine.
[scoffs]

16:01.584 --> 16:04.086
It's all fine, really.
She's just--

16:04.086 --> 16:06.755
she's a little emotional
right now, but--I'm sorry.

16:06.755 --> 16:09.258
- Go by Cossetta's on 7th
while you're out there.

16:09.258 --> 16:12.094
Bring her back something sweet.
- I will.

16:12.094 --> 16:13.596
Thank you.
I'm sorry.

16:13.596 --> 16:16.849
I told her
not to do this anymore.

16:26.358 --> 16:30.154
[telephone ringing]

16:40.539 --> 16:42.917
[ringing softens]

16:42.917 --> 16:46.003
[mysterious music]

16:46.003 --> 16:48.964
[ringing continues softly]

16:48.964 --> 16:52.051
[line trilling]

16:52.051 --> 16:55.638
[pen clicking]

16:57.556 --> 16:59.975
[ringing continues]

16:59.975 --> 17:01.936
CANDY: So next time
when you're feeling sad

17:01.936 --> 17:04.188
because you didn't get
what you want,

17:04.188 --> 17:07.483
you just wait...

17:07.483 --> 17:11.320
'cause God has something
even better for you.

17:22.414 --> 17:23.958
I have to call Sherry
and tell her

17:23.958 --> 17:25.459
I can't drop off
the card table.

17:25.459 --> 17:27.211
She can swing by the house
and get it.

17:27.211 --> 17:29.338
But if I leave now to get
Christina's bathing suit--

17:29.338 --> 17:30.673
oh, Betty told me
to come at noon,

17:30.673 --> 17:32.591
but now works better for me,
when I think of it.

17:32.591 --> 17:34.551
- Miss Betty--
Jesus forgive me,

17:34.551 --> 17:36.553
but I can never tell
if she loves children too much

17:36.553 --> 17:38.305
or not at all.
- [chuckles]

17:38.305 --> 17:40.099
Oh, she just needs
to loosen up.

17:40.099 --> 17:41.100
- Mm.

17:41.100 --> 17:43.394
- No, besides, if I leave now,

17:43.394 --> 17:45.563
I might have time
to stop at Target

17:45.563 --> 17:47.189
and pick up Father's Day cards

17:47.189 --> 17:49.191
for the kids on the way back,
then pick up the kids,

17:49.191 --> 17:51.151
then home to change,
then go to the pool,

17:51.151 --> 17:52.528
then back home to change again

17:52.528 --> 17:54.196
before we meet Pat for dinner
and the movie.

17:54.196 --> 17:57.032
- Lord, you make me tired
just listening to you.

17:57.032 --> 17:59.410
But look at you--
you can do it all, Miss Candy.

17:59.410 --> 18:02.037
- Well, it's nothing
if I can keep it all straight.

18:02.037 --> 18:04.373
- Well, just mind you get back
in time to see the pageant.

18:04.373 --> 18:06.125
Should be cute.

18:06.125 --> 18:08.502
- Oh, I will be back for that.
Should only be an hour or so.

18:08.502 --> 18:10.087
That's why I'm going
to the Plano Target.

18:10.087 --> 18:11.380
- Mm, smart.

18:11.380 --> 18:13.257
- All right,
well, I'm gonna git.

18:16.385 --> 18:19.388
[distant dog barking]

18:27.062 --> 18:28.397
Hey, y'all.

18:44.079 --> 18:45.706
[soft piano music playing]

18:45.706 --> 18:47.708
PERSON: Smile big.
[indistinct chatter]

18:47.708 --> 18:49.376
- Yes, dear.

18:49.376 --> 18:51.211
- Have you seen my mother?

18:51.211 --> 18:52.838
- I know she had
some things to do,

18:52.838 --> 18:54.673
but she said she'll be back.

18:54.673 --> 18:56.800
PERSON: Okay, everyone,
we're about to get started.

18:56.800 --> 18:58.927
[distressing music]

18:58.927 --> 19:02.431
[cheers and applause]

19:02.431 --> 19:04.475
[tires squeal]

19:04.475 --> 19:11.523
♪ ♪

19:37.424 --> 19:39.885
- [mouths word]

19:39.885 --> 19:46.892
♪ ♪

20:10.165 --> 20:14.586
JASON: Bears, cats,

20:14.586 --> 20:15.796
cows...

20:15.796 --> 20:17.381
[upbeat piano music playing]

20:17.381 --> 20:19.049
- Aiden...
JASON: Lions...

20:19.049 --> 20:21.468
♪ ♪

20:21.468 --> 20:22.803
Penguins.

20:24.847 --> 20:27.850
[distressing music]

20:27.850 --> 20:32.729
♪ ♪

20:32.729 --> 20:35.858
Giraffes, dinosaurs.

20:35.858 --> 20:42.865
♪ ♪

20:44.241 --> 20:46.952
Bunnies...

20:46.952 --> 20:49.371
elephant.

20:49.371 --> 20:52.082
[applause]

20:52.082 --> 20:57.713
♪ ♪

20:57.713 --> 20:59.715
[doorbell rings]

21:02.676 --> 21:05.304
[doorbell ringing]

21:08.223 --> 21:12.186
♪ ♪

21:12.186 --> 21:14.646
- Christina!

21:14.646 --> 21:21.653
♪ ♪

21:44.968 --> 21:48.388
- Candy, oh, my God,
where have you been?

21:48.388 --> 21:51.099
[sighs] Becky noticed
that you missed the pageant.

21:51.099 --> 21:53.227
Not sure if little Jason did
'cause he was--

21:53.227 --> 21:55.479
- Well, Betty and I
got to talking,

21:55.479 --> 21:57.272
and then I went down
to the Target in Plano,

21:57.272 --> 21:58.941
like I said,
and you will not believe,

21:58.941 --> 22:01.568
when I got there, I realized
my watch had stopped,

22:01.568 --> 22:03.320
and then I felt like
I had been gone too long.

22:03.320 --> 22:05.572
So I didn't even go in.
I just came right back here.

22:05.572 --> 22:07.991
And now I guess I'm just gonna
have to make it up to 'em.

22:07.991 --> 22:10.827
- Okay, well, calm down, now.
Nobody's judging you.

22:10.827 --> 22:12.329
Can't be perfect all the time.

22:12.329 --> 22:15.457
- Oh, aren't your little
sneakers so darling?

22:15.457 --> 22:17.543
I'm used to seeing
your old beat-up shower shoes.

22:17.543 --> 22:20.879
LINDA: [laughs]
- Thank you.

22:20.879 --> 22:23.674
- Here you go, hon.
- Thank you.

22:23.674 --> 22:25.092
Oh.

22:25.092 --> 22:28.011
BECKY: Mom.
- Hi, baby. I am so sorry.

22:28.011 --> 22:29.638
I went to get
Christina's bathing suit

22:29.638 --> 22:32.391
and then to the Target in Plano
to get your Father's Day cards,

22:32.391 --> 22:34.643
but my watch stopped,
and I lost track of time,

22:34.643 --> 22:36.895
and I got here
as soon as I could.

22:36.895 --> 22:39.147
- I wanted to pick out
my own card.

22:39.147 --> 22:41.191
- Oh, well, of course.

22:41.191 --> 22:44.152
Let's go do that
after we're done eating, okay?

22:44.152 --> 22:45.571
Okay.

22:51.702 --> 22:54.705
[bright Muzak playing]

22:54.705 --> 22:57.708
♪ ♪

22:57.708 --> 23:00.377
[cash register whirring,
beeping]

23:00.377 --> 23:03.630
- Ooh! Ooh! Mom?
- Third world babies.

23:03.630 --> 23:05.632
JASON: Aw.
[children laugh]

23:05.632 --> 23:12.639
♪ ♪

23:18.270 --> 23:21.523
[cash register whirring,
beeping]

23:21.523 --> 23:28.530
♪ ♪

23:28.530 --> 23:31.199
[children laughing]

23:31.199 --> 23:37.956
♪ ♪

23:37.956 --> 23:40.959
- Come on,
let's get something sweet.

23:46.340 --> 23:50.260
[dogs whining]

23:53.096 --> 23:56.099
[light music]

23:56.099 --> 24:03.148
♪ ♪

24:09.655 --> 24:13.200
- Becky, help Christina
get ready for swim.

24:13.200 --> 24:20.207
♪ ♪

24:25.045 --> 24:28.048
[line trilling]
[sniffs]

24:34.012 --> 24:36.139
- Pat Montgomery.
- Hi, hon.

24:36.139 --> 24:37.975
- Oh, hi, hon.
What's going on?

24:37.975 --> 24:40.811
- Uh, Christina will be coming
to the movie with us tonight

24:40.811 --> 24:42.646
and spending the night again,
and I was wondering

24:42.646 --> 24:44.398
if you could go to the bank
and get some more cash

24:44.398 --> 24:46.191
'cause I'm just not gonna
have enough time,

24:46.191 --> 24:48.360
because I got to talking
to Betty, and I just--

24:48.360 --> 24:49.528
I ran later than I thought,

24:49.528 --> 24:50.904
and then when I went
down to Target

24:50.904 --> 24:53.281
and, when I got there,
realized my watch had stopped,

24:53.281 --> 24:54.700
and I didn't even go in.

24:54.700 --> 24:56.076
I just went straight back
to the church,

24:56.076 --> 24:57.369
and I missed the kids' pageant,

24:57.369 --> 24:59.371
but I did get
Christina's bathing suit.

24:59.371 --> 25:01.665
And now we're back here
at the house, and I'm just--

25:01.665 --> 25:03.667
got to get these kids
out to the pool.

25:03.667 --> 25:05.419
And then I got to find time
to go get gas

25:05.419 --> 25:06.753
before we head down to see you,

25:06.753 --> 25:08.171
and then of course
we're gonna come back

25:08.171 --> 25:09.756
to the house to change
after the pool before,

25:09.756 --> 25:13.552
so do you think you could
make it to the bank?

25:13.552 --> 25:14.928
- Sure.
That's a lot.

25:14.928 --> 25:17.973
You okay?
- I'm fine. I'm fine.

25:17.973 --> 25:20.434
Just some suburban
car calculus.

25:20.434 --> 25:22.144
- [chuckles]
Yeah, we're living the dream.

25:22.144 --> 25:23.603
CANDY: We are.

25:23.603 --> 25:25.814
Hey, do you know where
Allan Gore's working today?

25:29.735 --> 25:30.861
- No.
Why?

25:32.654 --> 25:35.198
- Never mind.
Bye.

25:35.198 --> 25:36.616
[line clicks]
- Bye.

25:46.209 --> 25:49.629
[indistinct chatter]

25:49.629 --> 25:52.883
[mysterious music]

25:52.883 --> 25:57.512
♪ ♪

25:57.512 --> 25:59.931
- Good afternoon, sir.
How can I help you?

25:59.931 --> 26:02.100
- Uh, I would like to buy
some traveler's checks.

26:02.100 --> 26:03.101
- Of course.

26:03.101 --> 26:04.478
How much
would you like to spend

26:04.478 --> 26:05.687
and in which denomination?

26:05.687 --> 26:08.065
- 700 British pounds, please.

26:09.733 --> 26:11.026
- Do you hold an account
with us?

26:11.026 --> 26:13.069
- Oh.
[chuckles]

26:13.069 --> 26:15.447
Yes, of course.
Here's my card.

26:17.991 --> 26:22.245
My wife is gonna be so pleased
to get these check numbers.

26:22.245 --> 26:24.664
I think it's gonna make
the trip more real for her,

26:24.664 --> 26:25.874
you know?

26:25.874 --> 26:28.001
- Lovely.
Going to England?

26:28.001 --> 26:32.005
- No, Switzerland.
Sort of a second honeymoon.

26:32.005 --> 26:34.758
We were there, uh,
shortly after our wedding.

26:34.758 --> 26:38.095
I was, uh,
on a work assignment.

26:38.095 --> 26:40.472
One of the happiest times
of our life.

26:41.932 --> 26:43.558
Might as well go back, right?

26:43.558 --> 26:46.144
- They say
you can always go back.

26:46.144 --> 26:48.105
- Do they?

26:48.105 --> 26:50.232
Yeah--yeah, where is that from?

26:50.232 --> 26:53.944
- I don't know,
but, uh, I've heard it.

26:53.944 --> 26:56.571
- Yeah. Well, it works for me.
[chuckles]

26:56.571 --> 26:58.782
- Now, do make a note
of the numbers on these checks.

26:58.782 --> 27:00.158
If they are lost or misplaced,

27:00.158 --> 27:01.827
they can be canceled
and replaced.

27:01.827 --> 27:04.579
- Yes, I am going
to call my wife right now

27:04.579 --> 27:06.581
and give her these numbers.

27:06.581 --> 27:07.749
Thank you.

27:07.749 --> 27:10.710
[indistinct chatter]

27:20.428 --> 27:23.431
[telephone ringing]

27:34.734 --> 27:38.822
[baby crying]

27:38.822 --> 27:41.825
[ringing continues]

27:47.956 --> 27:50.917
[soft, pleasant music]

27:50.917 --> 27:57.924
♪ ♪

28:18.194 --> 28:19.404
SHERRY: Hey, y'all.

28:19.404 --> 28:21.031
- Hey.
SHERRY: Hi, hon.

28:21.031 --> 28:22.699
You know, I was thinking
about it,

28:22.699 --> 28:24.826
and I think we're meant to hate

28:24.826 --> 28:26.828
Kristen's Ewing Oil condo,
but I don't know.

28:26.828 --> 28:28.371
I mean, I know that it's dated,

28:28.371 --> 28:30.206
but what's so wrong
with--with old things?

28:30.206 --> 28:32.292
I mean, people thought they
were beautiful at one point.

28:32.292 --> 28:35.086
But besides that,
that whole affair is just--hoo!

28:35.086 --> 28:38.506
Sometimes I think even I could
go for a-a strong, bad man

28:38.506 --> 28:39.925
who goes after what he wants,

28:39.925 --> 28:41.551
even if it is
his wife's evil sister.

28:41.551 --> 28:43.261
[chuckles]
And that mother of theirs--

28:43.261 --> 28:46.348
so overbearing, sweet Jesus.

28:46.348 --> 28:48.600
My, my, what is wrong?

28:49.768 --> 28:50.810
- Nothing.
SHERRY: What?

28:50.810 --> 28:52.437
No, come on now,
miss girly-girl.

28:52.437 --> 28:55.190
You tell me everything.
- [scoffs]

28:55.190 --> 28:57.525
Just too much coffee,
I suppose.

28:57.525 --> 28:59.402
- Well, I'm not
buying that, hon.

28:59.402 --> 29:01.947
All right, look, let me get
the in-laws out of the house,

29:01.947 --> 29:04.115
and then when I come back
and return the table,

29:04.115 --> 29:06.618
we'll have a nice long gab
about whatever this is.

29:06.618 --> 29:09.579
- I'm fine.
- All right, kisses.

29:12.999 --> 29:16.002
[children chattering outside]

29:16.002 --> 29:19.005
[front door clicks]

29:20.966 --> 29:23.885
[children laughing outside]

29:23.885 --> 29:27.097
[tense music]

29:27.097 --> 29:29.516
ANNOUNCER: Final boarding
for flight 892,

29:29.516 --> 29:32.352
Minneapolis, Saint Paul--
gate B13.

29:32.352 --> 29:39.401
♪ ♪

29:48.994 --> 29:51.663
JASON: Hey. Hey. Hey!

29:51.663 --> 29:54.541
Remember that guy who was
roller-skating down the hall,

29:54.541 --> 29:56.292
and he turned around,
and he went like this...

29:56.292 --> 29:58.586
BECKY:
Mom, he's doing it again.

29:58.586 --> 29:59.963
CHRISTINA: What does that mean?

29:59.963 --> 30:02.507
BECKY: It's bad, and he's not
supposed to be doing it.

30:02.507 --> 30:03.925
Mom.
- [breathing heavily]

30:03.925 --> 30:05.468
CHRISTINA: I'm gonna do it
to baby Valerie.

30:05.468 --> 30:07.220
All she does is cry.

30:07.220 --> 30:10.557
[imitating crying]

30:10.557 --> 30:13.852
[all imitating crying]

30:13.852 --> 30:16.896
[baby crying]

30:25.613 --> 30:27.657
[knock on window]

30:27.657 --> 30:28.825
- You getting a quick nap?

30:28.825 --> 30:30.076
JASON: Daddy!
PAT: Yeah.

30:30.076 --> 30:31.411
Oh, ew.

30:31.411 --> 30:32.871
I didn't think
the kids would be here.

30:32.871 --> 30:34.205
- [laughs]
JASON: No!

30:34.205 --> 30:36.416
We're going to see
Star Wars, remember?

30:36.416 --> 30:37.792
We said that this morning.

30:37.792 --> 30:40.253
PAT: I know. I'm joking, sport.
- [Candy laughs]

30:40.253 --> 30:42.172
- Hey, 5:15 hasn't started yet,

30:42.172 --> 30:43.590
and there are
still tickets left.

30:43.590 --> 30:45.425
Why don't we go see the movie
now and eat afterwards?

30:45.425 --> 30:47.010
[children cheering]
Yeah? All right.

30:47.010 --> 30:48.470
BECKY: Come on!
CANDY: Okay, let's go.

30:48.470 --> 30:49.846
I'm sorry I'm taking so long.

30:49.846 --> 30:51.765
Let's go.
PAT: Climb on out here, buddy.

30:51.765 --> 30:53.308
CANDY: Oh, you guys,
you're so excited.

30:53.308 --> 30:55.769
- You got your lightsaber?
BECKY: Come on!

30:55.769 --> 30:57.103
PAT: All right,
be careful with that.

30:57.103 --> 30:59.481
JASON: Wait for me, Becky!
BECKY: Come on!

31:02.901 --> 31:04.778
ALLAN: All right, perfect.
Thank you.

31:04.778 --> 31:06.488
[clears throat]

31:06.488 --> 31:08.948
SID: Hey, you mind
if we wait on dinner?

31:08.948 --> 31:11.159
I got to get a jog in.
I brought my Tigers.

31:11.159 --> 31:12.535
They got reflectors
in the back,

31:12.535 --> 31:14.329
in case it gets dark.

31:14.329 --> 31:16.581
You're welcome to join.
- No, that's all right.

31:16.581 --> 31:18.666
I'm gonna head upstairs,
try Betty again,

31:18.666 --> 31:21.002
but just give me a call
when you're ready to eat, yeah?

31:21.002 --> 31:23.129
- Yeah, okay.

31:23.129 --> 31:25.131
[door closes]

31:25.131 --> 31:28.134
[tense music]

31:28.134 --> 31:33.139
♪ ♪

31:33.139 --> 31:35.350
- [sighs]

31:38.353 --> 31:40.063
Hello, Operator?

31:40.063 --> 31:41.815
I'm wondering if you could
help me place a call.

31:41.815 --> 31:45.110
I'm having a bit of a hard time
getting through.

31:45.110 --> 31:47.529
Wylie, Texas.

31:47.529 --> 31:50.907
Allan Gore residence.

31:50.907 --> 31:52.242
Thank you.

31:52.242 --> 31:59.249
♪ ♪

32:04.546 --> 32:07.382
Oh, um...no, thank you.

32:07.382 --> 32:10.093
I-I'll just try back later.

32:10.093 --> 32:11.386
All right.

32:11.386 --> 32:17.725
♪ ♪

32:17.725 --> 32:20.728
[laughter, indistinct chatter]

32:22.939 --> 32:24.440
[both imitate
lightsabers clashing]

32:24.440 --> 32:27.068
JASON: But Dad, is Han dead?
- [exhales deeply]

32:27.068 --> 32:29.445
PAT: No, they wouldn't do that.

32:29.445 --> 32:33.032
- I cut off your hand!
CHRISTINA: No!

32:33.032 --> 32:34.325
- [retches]

32:34.325 --> 32:36.995
JASON: Why does Princess Leia
hate him so much?

32:36.995 --> 32:38.872
PAT: I don't think
she hates him.

32:38.872 --> 32:40.874
I think she might love him.

32:40.874 --> 32:42.375
JASON: No, I don't want
the love stuff.

32:42.375 --> 32:43.543
- [Candy coughs]

32:43.543 --> 32:45.170
- [as Darth Vader]
Jason, I am your father,

32:45.170 --> 32:46.546
and I love you.

32:46.546 --> 32:48.965
JASON: No!
- [laughs]

32:48.965 --> 32:50.884
- You okay?
You look like you're limping.

32:50.884 --> 32:54.262
- Oh, uh, I cut my toe
on the storm door earlier.

32:54.262 --> 32:55.847
You know, the one
I asked you to fix?

32:55.847 --> 32:57.849
- Oh, you did.
I'm sorry.

32:57.849 --> 32:59.809
This weekend, I promise.
- Okay.

32:59.809 --> 33:02.187
- Hey, I forget.
Does anybody like tacos?

33:02.187 --> 33:03.897
JASON: Tacos, tacos, tacos!

33:03.897 --> 33:05.398
- All right, I'll pick 'em up.
I'll meet you at home.

33:05.398 --> 33:07.192
CANDY: Okay.
JASON: I want to come.

33:07.192 --> 33:08.860
- Yeah, I'll take him.
You take the girls.

33:08.860 --> 33:10.445
- Yep.
[laughter]

33:10.445 --> 33:11.905
- Are you okay?

33:11.905 --> 33:13.990
- I'm fine.
I'll see you at home.

33:13.990 --> 33:16.784
[soft music]

33:16.784 --> 33:20.330
BECKY: Mom, when we get home,
can we play dress-up?

33:20.330 --> 33:21.581
- Mm-hmm.

33:21.581 --> 33:23.708
♪ ♪

33:23.708 --> 33:25.251
CHRISTINA:
Can you do my makeup?

33:25.251 --> 33:26.753
BECKY:
Yeah, I'm good at it.

33:26.753 --> 33:29.464
CHRISTINA: My mom says
ladies pinch their cheeks.

33:29.464 --> 33:30.715
They don't use rouge.

33:30.715 --> 33:31.966
- [Becky laughs]

33:31.966 --> 33:33.551
- That's ridiculous.

33:33.551 --> 33:40.558
♪ ♪

33:48.233 --> 33:52.237
[baby crying]

33:57.951 --> 33:59.953
[door slams]
- [Pat grunts]

33:59.953 --> 34:01.496
Four miles.

34:01.496 --> 34:03.373
I'm really getting
my conditioning up.

34:03.373 --> 34:05.291
- Proud of you, baby.
- Thank you.

34:06.876 --> 34:09.879
[telephone ringing]

34:09.879 --> 34:12.882
[folk music playing softly]

34:12.882 --> 34:14.842
♪ ♪

34:14.842 --> 34:18.054
- Hello?
- Hey, Candy, it's Allan.

34:18.054 --> 34:19.931
- Oh.

34:19.931 --> 34:21.266
Well, hi, Allan.

34:21.266 --> 34:23.434
W-where are you?

34:23.434 --> 34:25.645
- Oh, I'm in, um--
I'm in Saint Paul.

34:25.645 --> 34:29.399
Hey, have you seen Betty
at all today?

34:29.399 --> 34:31.150
- Uh, well, I did see her
this morning

34:31.150 --> 34:32.819
when I went to get
Christina's bathing suit.

34:32.819 --> 34:34.904
She's here with us,
staying another night.

34:34.904 --> 34:36.155
- I...

34:37.991 --> 34:39.534
Did she seem all right?

34:41.077 --> 34:42.996
- Well, yeah, she seemed fine.

34:44.872 --> 34:47.208
Christina's here with us,
staying another night.

34:47.208 --> 34:48.710
Would you like
to speak to her?

34:48.710 --> 34:52.672
- Um...yes.
Thanks.

34:52.672 --> 34:54.382
- Christina,
your daddy's on the phone.

34:54.382 --> 34:56.050
Come say hi.

35:00.013 --> 35:01.764
Just a sec.

35:04.350 --> 35:06.436
- Yep.

35:06.436 --> 35:09.647
SINGER:
♪ It's tearing me apart ♪

35:09.647 --> 35:12.609
- Hi, Daddy.
- Hey, sweetheart.

35:12.609 --> 35:15.194
Are you having fun?
CHRISTINA: Yes. Candy--

35:15.194 --> 35:16.279
- Miss Candy.

35:16.279 --> 35:18.239
- Miss Candy took me
to swimming,

35:18.239 --> 35:20.033
and then I went under
and had a mint.

35:20.033 --> 35:21.826
- Well, I hope you had
some dinner, too.

35:21.826 --> 35:24.662
CHRISTINA: Yes, we had tacos.
- Good.

35:29.125 --> 35:31.711
Well...

35:31.711 --> 35:32.837
night-night.

35:32.837 --> 35:34.797
- Okay, love you.

35:36.174 --> 35:37.800
CANDY: Hey, Allan.
- Hey.

35:37.800 --> 35:41.346
- Is everything all right?
ALLAN: I'm sure it is.

35:41.346 --> 35:44.182
Betty's not answering
the phone.

35:44.182 --> 35:46.601
- Oh.

35:46.601 --> 35:48.811
Would you like me
to go over there?

35:48.811 --> 35:52.190
- No, I'm sure
everything's fine.

35:52.190 --> 35:53.900
I'll have a neighbor
do that, though.

35:53.900 --> 35:56.110
- Well, okay.
[chuckles]

35:56.110 --> 35:57.362
If you change your mind...

35:57.362 --> 35:59.655
- Oh, I'm sure
everything's fine.

36:01.991 --> 36:04.327
Thanks, Candy.

36:04.327 --> 36:06.496
- Oh, you're welcome.

36:06.496 --> 36:08.665
- Bye.
- Okay, bye.

36:08.665 --> 36:12.085
♪ ♪

36:12.085 --> 36:14.087
- What was that all about?

36:14.087 --> 36:16.297
- He just said Betty wasn't
answering the phone.

36:16.297 --> 36:18.591
I mean, she seemed fine
when I saw her this morning,

36:18.591 --> 36:20.343
but then I went to Target,
and I realized

36:20.343 --> 36:21.677
my watch had stopped.

36:21.677 --> 36:23.638
I didn't even go in. I just--
[scoffs]

36:23.638 --> 36:27.392
Just went right back
to the church to get the kids.

36:27.392 --> 36:29.060
- You said that before.

36:30.436 --> 36:32.021
- Did I?

36:32.021 --> 36:33.022
Hmm.

36:37.068 --> 36:39.278
- Hello, I'm--I'm looking
for a phone number

36:39.278 --> 36:42.240
for Richard Parker
in Wylie, Texas.

36:44.117 --> 36:46.869
Oh, sorry.
Hang on one second.

36:46.869 --> 36:49.038
Yeah, go ahead.

36:49.038 --> 36:51.165
Okay.

36:51.165 --> 36:52.917
Perfect.
Thank you so much.

36:52.917 --> 36:56.087
[telephone ringing]

36:56.087 --> 36:59.507
[sports announcer speaking
indistinctly on TV]

36:59.507 --> 37:02.510
[ringing continues]

37:06.889 --> 37:07.974
- Hello?

37:07.974 --> 37:10.059
- Hey, Richard,
this is Allan Gore

37:10.059 --> 37:11.727
from, uh, across the street.

37:11.727 --> 37:13.396
- Uh, hey, Allan.

37:13.396 --> 37:15.356
ALLAN: Hey, I'm really glad
you're home.

37:15.356 --> 37:17.024
Could I ask you for a favor?

37:17.024 --> 37:19.652
I was wondering if you
wouldn't mind just popping

37:19.652 --> 37:21.404
across the street
and checking on Betty for me.

37:21.404 --> 37:22.822
- Uh...
ALLAN: She's not answering

37:22.822 --> 37:26.117
the phone, and, um...
I'm a little worried about it.

37:26.117 --> 37:28.661
- Yeah, uh, I got
the kids here, Allan.

37:28.661 --> 37:31.247
- I promise I wouldn't ask
if it wasn't important.

37:31.247 --> 37:33.166
- It's the wife's
bridge night, so...

37:33.166 --> 37:34.542
ALLAN: I get it.

37:34.542 --> 37:36.377
Richard, I'm in Saint Paul
on business,

37:36.377 --> 37:38.129
and, you know,
I've been calling her all day.

37:38.129 --> 37:41.549
She always answers the phone,
and, um, she's not.

37:41.549 --> 37:44.802
So I could really use
your help, Richard,

37:44.802 --> 37:47.096
if you don't mind.

37:47.096 --> 37:50.183
- Uh, yeah.
Okay.

37:50.183 --> 37:51.559
- Okay.

37:51.559 --> 37:54.937
- I can't, uh--I can't do it
just right yet, Allan,

37:54.937 --> 37:56.564
but, uh, I will.

38:04.614 --> 38:07.617
[telephone ringing]

38:20.463 --> 38:22.340
- Hello?

38:22.340 --> 38:23.883
[exhales deeply]

38:23.883 --> 38:25.676
Sid.

38:25.676 --> 38:28.346
Yeah. Yeah, of course.
I'll be right down.

38:32.308 --> 38:34.894
[sighs]

38:34.894 --> 38:36.813
SID: Hey.
- Hey.

38:36.813 --> 38:38.356
- You ready? I called.

38:38.356 --> 38:39.899
The restaurant's still serving.

38:39.899 --> 38:43.819
- Hi. Uh, Allan Gore, room 217.

38:43.819 --> 38:46.280
I'm wondering if you could have
any calls that come in for me

38:46.280 --> 38:48.533
just forwarded
to the restaurant.

38:48.533 --> 38:50.618
- Yes, sir.
- Thank you.

38:50.618 --> 38:52.829
- [sighs] Man...

38:52.829 --> 38:54.247
I really worked up an appetite.

38:54.247 --> 38:56.999
- Oh. Yeah.
Yep.

38:56.999 --> 39:00.545
- Good evening, gentlemen.
What can I bring you?

39:00.545 --> 39:02.088
- Uh, I'm Allan Gore.

39:04.006 --> 39:05.841
Just in case
a phone call comes in.

39:05.841 --> 39:07.802
Has a phone call
come in for me?

39:07.802 --> 39:09.053
- Not that I know of,

39:09.053 --> 39:11.097
but we'll keep
an ear out for you.

39:11.097 --> 39:12.974
Can I get you something to eat?

39:12.974 --> 39:16.269
SID: Yeah, um,
it's not on the menu,

39:16.269 --> 39:18.521
but could I possibly just have

39:18.521 --> 39:21.023
some steamed chicken--
just, like, a half chicken.

39:21.023 --> 39:22.525
WAITRESS: Okay.
SYD: Vegetables.

39:22.525 --> 39:24.902
Or baked--baked is fine,
but steamed, if you can.

39:24.902 --> 39:27.071
WAITRESS: Uh, I'll go check
and come back.

39:27.071 --> 39:28.781
I'm sure we can
work something out.

39:28.781 --> 39:31.784
[disquieting music]

39:31.784 --> 39:34.787
[intense whirring]

39:34.787 --> 39:37.957
♪ ♪

39:37.957 --> 39:40.126
And for you, sir?

39:40.126 --> 39:41.669
- Oh.

39:41.669 --> 39:44.505
I'm--I'm not really
that hungry right now,

39:44.505 --> 39:46.507
but maybe--

39:46.507 --> 39:48.467
maybe just a slice
of cheesecake.

39:48.467 --> 39:52.430
- All right,
that is my kind of dinner.

39:54.390 --> 39:56.309
- Cheesecake.

39:56.309 --> 39:58.102
Man, I wish
I could eat like that,

39:58.102 --> 39:59.395
but those 15 pounds,
they're not gonna

39:59.395 --> 40:00.855
keep themselves off, you know?

40:00.855 --> 40:03.566
- Uh, you look great.
SID: Thanks, buddy.

40:03.566 --> 40:05.318
You know, it makes
the soreness worth it.

40:05.318 --> 40:07.028
[inaudible conversation]

40:09.363 --> 40:10.531
You try her friends?

40:10.531 --> 40:13.367
- Oh, she doesn't really
have any friends.

40:13.367 --> 40:15.369
She never leaves
the house at night, so...

40:15.369 --> 40:16.954
- Uh, Mr. Gore,
the front desk said

40:16.954 --> 40:18.497
a Richard Parker
called for you.

40:18.497 --> 40:20.207
Said to call back when you can.
- Thank you.

40:20.207 --> 40:23.085
Uh, I'm gonna--I'm gonna go.

40:23.085 --> 40:24.629
- What about your cake?

40:24.629 --> 40:25.963
- You can just have them,

40:25.963 --> 40:27.381
uh, send it up to the room,
I guess.

40:27.381 --> 40:28.799
Thank you.

40:31.802 --> 40:34.805
[keypad beeping]

40:37.308 --> 40:41.354
[line trilling]
[inhales deeply]

40:41.354 --> 40:44.398
[telephone ringing]

40:44.398 --> 40:46.150
- Hey, Allan.
- Hey, Richard.

40:46.150 --> 40:47.610
RICHARD: Hey.
- Hey.

40:47.610 --> 40:49.820
RICHARD: Uh, yeah,
I, uh, knocked real hard there

40:49.820 --> 40:51.447
a couple times, and, uh--
- Okay, and?

40:51.447 --> 40:54.992
- Nothing, uh, but your
small car is gone, though,

40:54.992 --> 40:57.536
so she must be out.

40:59.538 --> 41:02.917
- Um...
do you have a phone book...

41:02.917 --> 41:04.293
[clears throat]
Nearby?

41:04.293 --> 41:06.253
Would you mind
just flipping through

41:06.253 --> 41:07.463
and giving me
a couple numbers?

41:07.463 --> 41:09.715
Give me the number
for Medical City

41:09.715 --> 41:11.926
and, uh...

41:11.926 --> 41:14.136
maybe the Wylie Police?

41:14.136 --> 41:15.805
RICHARD: Just a sec.

41:17.848 --> 41:20.851
[dramatic music]

41:20.851 --> 41:27.900
♪ ♪

41:59.223 --> 42:02.226
[line trilling]

42:04.562 --> 42:06.439
[line clicks]
CANDY: Hello?

42:06.439 --> 42:07.815
- Candy.

42:07.815 --> 42:09.817
- Allan, is everything
all right?

42:09.817 --> 42:11.277
Did you find Betty?

42:11.277 --> 42:13.738
- No, I, uh...

42:13.738 --> 42:15.281
[chuckles]

42:15.281 --> 42:18.409
I called the hospital
and I called the police,

42:18.409 --> 42:21.078
and neither of them know
where she is,

42:21.078 --> 42:23.456
or the baby.

42:23.456 --> 42:25.416
- [Candy sighs]

42:25.416 --> 42:27.043
I should go over there.

42:27.043 --> 42:30.296
Do you want me
to go over there?

42:30.296 --> 42:33.799
- No, I'm gonna have
a neighbor go again.

42:36.594 --> 42:39.555
- Oh, Allan.
[sniffs]

42:41.974 --> 42:45.061
- Thanks, Candy.

42:45.061 --> 42:47.271
Good night.

42:47.271 --> 42:49.023
- Good night.

42:49.023 --> 42:56.030
♪ ♪

43:05.372 --> 43:07.166
- [groans]

43:08.626 --> 43:11.629
[splutters, sighs]

43:14.840 --> 43:17.843
[keypad beeping]

43:19.887 --> 43:22.890
[line trilling]

43:27.228 --> 43:31.023
[telephone ringing]

43:31.023 --> 43:32.316
- Hello?

43:32.316 --> 43:35.569
- Hey, it's me again.
I'm so sorry, Richard.

43:35.569 --> 43:37.947
Would you mind just going
over there one more time?

43:37.947 --> 43:39.532
Maybe she fell.
- [sighs]

43:39.532 --> 43:41.283
ALLAN: And just check
all the doors?

43:42.910 --> 43:45.579
Please?

43:45.579 --> 43:48.040
- Yeah.
All right.

43:48.040 --> 43:50.459
Um, just hold on.
- Thank you.

43:50.459 --> 43:52.670
[sports announcer speaking
indistinctly on TV]

43:52.670 --> 43:54.088
- [groans]

43:56.131 --> 44:03.139
♪ ♪

44:26.912 --> 44:28.998
Hey, Allan?
- Yeah.

44:28.998 --> 44:32.251
- Uh, her car is there.
I just hadn't seen it before.

44:32.251 --> 44:34.128
It was pulled all the way up.

44:34.128 --> 44:35.671
Now, the lights are on,

44:35.671 --> 44:38.048
but it doesn't seem
like anyone's home.

44:38.048 --> 44:41.677
- I need you to get
into that house, Richard.

44:41.677 --> 44:43.637
I don't care how you do it.

44:43.637 --> 44:45.556
- Uh, okay.
Yeah.

44:45.556 --> 44:48.601
Um, you know, I might still
have my, uh, realtor's key.

44:48.601 --> 44:51.520
- Break a goddamn window
if you have to.

44:51.520 --> 44:53.772
Just get into that house.

45:08.996 --> 45:11.415
JERRY: Richard?
- [sighs]

45:11.415 --> 45:13.834
Christ, Jerry,
what are you doing here?

45:13.834 --> 45:16.587
- Allan called, asked me
to check out the house.

45:16.587 --> 45:17.588
RICHARD: Same here.

45:19.924 --> 45:22.426
I don't know about this.

45:22.426 --> 45:23.802
- I feel it too.

45:27.014 --> 45:29.808
Ruth insisted I bring it.

45:29.808 --> 45:31.185
- Good.

45:31.185 --> 45:34.229
[distant dog barking]

45:45.449 --> 45:48.452
[unsettling music]

45:48.452 --> 45:55.417
♪ ♪

46:05.928 --> 46:07.221
[footsteps approach]

46:07.221 --> 46:08.806
- Whoa, whoa, it's me, Lester.

46:08.806 --> 46:11.684
- [sighs]
What are you doing here?

46:11.684 --> 46:14.436
- Ruth called. She was worried.
Asked me to come back you up.

46:14.436 --> 46:15.938
What's going on here?

46:15.938 --> 46:18.273
- Trying to find out.
It's weird.

46:18.273 --> 46:20.985
Allan can't get ahold of Betty,
but the car is here

46:20.985 --> 46:23.112
and the lights are on,
and no one's opening the door.

46:23.112 --> 46:26.490
- I got my key ring.
I'll see if one of these works.

46:26.490 --> 46:27.741
How about you two go out back

46:27.741 --> 46:29.702
and see if there's a window
or something?

46:29.702 --> 46:36.667
♪ ♪

46:40.587 --> 46:43.215
- [Lester groans]

46:43.215 --> 46:44.466
Watch your step.

46:44.466 --> 46:47.261
[dogs whine]

46:47.261 --> 46:54.268
♪ ♪

47:10.451 --> 47:13.329
- Jerry! Lester!

47:13.329 --> 47:19.001
♪ ♪

47:19.001 --> 47:21.253
The door was unlocked.

47:21.253 --> 47:27.301
♪ ♪

47:27.301 --> 47:28.719
Betty?

47:28.719 --> 47:35.726
♪ ♪

47:50.824 --> 47:52.451
LESTER: [whispering]
Hey, Richard.

47:52.451 --> 47:58.123
♪ ♪

47:58.123 --> 48:01.085
[baby crying hoarsely]

48:04.338 --> 48:06.131
- Oh, my God.

48:06.131 --> 48:08.634
Baby, come here.
- Oh, get her out of here.

48:08.634 --> 48:11.929
- Oh, Jesus.
Oh, no.

48:11.929 --> 48:14.389
- Oh, poor thing.
- [baby gurgles]

48:14.389 --> 48:17.935
- I got you.
I got you, baby.

48:17.935 --> 48:20.979
[unsettling music building]

48:20.979 --> 48:24.983
♪ ♪

48:24.983 --> 48:26.401
[door slams]

48:26.401 --> 48:28.654
Honey, take her.
[baby cries]

48:28.654 --> 48:31.156
- Lord, what's going on?
- Just see to her, all right?

48:31.156 --> 48:33.659
Call the police, and you
send 'em to the Gores' house.

48:33.659 --> 48:36.495
- Oh, what--
what are you getting that for?

48:36.495 --> 48:37.996
- Stay inside
with the doors locked

48:37.996 --> 48:39.081
till I come back, you hear?

48:39.081 --> 48:40.457
- Tell me what's going on,
baby.

48:40.457 --> 48:42.292
- Just lock the door behind me.
[baby crying]

48:42.292 --> 48:49.299
♪ ♪

49:27.546 --> 49:30.549
[keys jingling]

49:33.093 --> 49:40.100
♪ ♪

49:41.852 --> 49:45.105
LESTER: Oh, my God. Jeez.

49:45.105 --> 49:46.398
JERRY: What is it, Lester?

49:46.398 --> 49:53.405
♪ ♪

49:55.491 --> 49:57.326
Good God almighty.

49:57.326 --> 50:00.329
[telephone ringing]

50:09.129 --> 50:10.589
- Hello?

50:10.589 --> 50:13.383
- Hello?
This is Allan.

50:13.383 --> 50:14.593
- Allan.

50:21.475 --> 50:25.896
- [clears throat]
Allan, Jerry here.

50:25.896 --> 50:27.272
- Hey, Jerry.

50:27.272 --> 50:29.107
JERRY: Listen...

50:29.107 --> 50:31.902
it's not good.

50:31.902 --> 50:33.737
But the baby's okay.

50:37.783 --> 50:39.701
- What about Betty?

50:41.036 --> 50:44.206
- I'm sorry, Allan.
It looks like she's been shot.

50:48.210 --> 50:49.503
- Shot?

50:56.093 --> 50:58.387
We don't even own a gun.

50:58.387 --> 51:01.390
[dramatic music]

51:01.390 --> 51:08.438
♪ ♪

51:15.612 --> 51:18.115
[telephone ringing]

51:18.115 --> 51:25.122
♪ ♪

51:25.122 --> 51:28.083
[ringing continues]

51:38.385 --> 51:39.928
- Hello?

51:39.928 --> 51:42.556
- Candy.

51:42.556 --> 51:44.308
- [sighs]
Allan.

51:44.308 --> 51:45.976
ALLAN: It's Betty.

51:48.437 --> 51:50.188
She's dead.

51:53.609 --> 51:55.736
She's been shot.

51:55.736 --> 51:59.906
♪ ♪

51:59.906 --> 52:01.325
- Wait, shot?

52:01.325 --> 52:03.410
♪ ♪

52:03.410 --> 52:05.162
W-with a gun?

52:05.162 --> 52:06.621
ALLAN: Yeah.

52:09.833 --> 52:13.712
- [breathing heavily]

52:13.712 --> 52:15.714
Everything's gonna be
all right.

52:15.714 --> 52:18.717
[eerie, bright music]

52:18.717 --> 52:25.724
♪ ♪
